<p>I'm trying to extend a model in rails.</p>  <p>Model <code>User</code> uses table <code>users</code> in database with field <code>:username</code>, <code>:password</code>.</p>  <pre><code>class User &lt; ActiveRecord::Base end </code></pre>  <p>Model SuperUser uses table <code>super_users</code> in database with fields <code>:user_id</code>, <code>:name</code>:</p>  <pre><code>class SuperUser &lt; ActiveRecord::Base  belongs_to :user end </code></pre>  <p>I would like the <code>SuperUser</code> to be an extension of <code>User</code> so as to be able to do this :</p>  <pre><code>SuperUser.create(:name =&gt; "foo", :username =&gt; "bar", :password =&gt; "foobar") </code></pre>  <p>or when I fetch data to get something like this</p>  <pre><code>&gt; s = SuperUser.find 1 &gt; s.username &gt; "bar"     </code></pre>  <p>Has anyone any idea how I can do this?</p>